raw_output:
The poem that uses onomatopoeia is (B) Chariots rumbling; horses neighing;
Soldiers shouting martial cries;
Drums are sounding; trumpets braying;
Seas of glittering spears arise. 

Onomatopoeia is when language sounds like what it talks about. In this poem, the words used create sounds that mimic the actual sounds being described, such as "rumbling," "neighing," "shouting," "sounding," and "braying."
